{
  "text": "Changes in drug-taking behaviour might also influence transmission dynamics and introduce new pools of susceptible individuals within PWID populations. In our results, the drop of N e T around 2002 might be partly attributed to the shift in the Russian-Ukrainian drug scene towards stimulant drugs (associated with risky injecting behaviours [CITATION_1] ). Thus, settings with changing drug scenes, including changes in drug of choice or demographic changes, should also be addressed with basic prevention scale-up.",
